This is a major update,  thank you for your patience.

NOTE: this is the last one update for iOS7 system, we will drop iOS7 support on next update.

- The Copy service will be discontinued on May 1, 2016, so we removed Copy cloud service support.
- Added playlist renaming support.
- Added online viewing photos support for iCloud, FTP and SFTP.
- Added AV Streaming support for Dropbox, Box, Google Drive, OneDrive, Baidu Cloud, FTP, SFTP, WebDAV and Yandex cloud services.
- Redesigned core of the music player
  - added the most audio formats support.
  - added cloud files support, user can play local and cloud audio files in one style.
- Added non-native audio formats support for music playlist.
- Added "The default landscape mode" for video player.
- Improved the video streaming feature for SMB service.
- Added video thumbnail support for SFTP and SMB services.
- Added photo thumbnail support for SFTP service.

This is a major update, we recommend that everyone update.
- fixed some compatibility issues for iOS 10.
- fixed a now playing info update crash issue.
- fixed a background playback issue for m4a audio format.
- fixed a file permission issue for unarchiver.
- fixed a authentication issue for WebDAV client.
- fixed a credential lookup issue for FTP and SFTP clients.
- improved the thumbnails system, thumbnails will be shown in original aspect ratio rather than square.
- keep window's state of the cloud file manager when user leave it.
- improve UE of the file manager.
- re-design the Settings page.
- improve the name conflicts handler for local and cloud file manager, added "Rename" and "Apply to all files" options.
- added automatically load subtitle support for video player.
- added RAR5 format support.
- added name conflicts options for unarchiver.
- added "Delete" op-menu for cloud photos browser.
